spirit:field.spirit:name: TAIL_POINTER_OFFSET
spirit:field.spirit:description: Submission Queue Tail Pointer Offset

spirit:field.spirit:name: INTERRUPT
spirit:field.spirit:description: Submission Queue Interrupt When set - and while the interrupt type in SQ_RESET_INTERRUPT_CTRL is 1 - triggers an interrupt on the submission queue. 0x0 - Do not trigger an interrupt on the submission queue 0x1 - Trigger an interrupt on the submission queue

spirit:field.spirit:name: MEM_ADDR_LOW
spirit:field.spirit:description: Submission Queue Memory Address Low Represents bits 31:0 of the submission queue device memory address.

spirit:register.spirit:name: SQ_RESET_INTERRUPT_CTRL
spirit:register.spirit:description: Submission Queue Reset and Interrupt Control

spirit:field.spirit:name: INTERRUPT_ENABLE
spirit:field.spirit:description: Submission Queue Interrupt Enable When set, enables interrupts for the submission queue. 0x0 - Disable submission queue interrupts 0x1 - Enable submission queue interrupts

spirit:field.spirit:name: INTERRUPT_TYPE
spirit:field.spirit:description: Submission Queue Interrupt Type Determines the interrupt type in use for the submission queue. 0x0 - Interrupts for the submission queue are triggered on a write operation to the tail pointer 0x1 - Interrupts for the submission queue are triggered by setting SQ_INTERRUPT_REG bit 0 high

spirit:field.spirit:name: RESET
spirit:field.spirit:description: Reset When set, performs a soft reset of all submission queue and completion queue registers.

spirit:field.spirit:name: MEM_ADDR_HIGH
spirit:field.spirit:description: Submission Queue Memory Address High Represents bits 63:32 of the submission queue device memory address.
